Invalid bundle for an in-toto DSSE envelope logged to Rekor v2 with the
new hashedrekord-over-DSSE encoding (kind=hashedrekord/0.0.2). The DSSE
envelope is valid in isolation and the payload is the same as what was
logged to Rekor, but the envelope signature does not match the signature
recorded in the tlog entry. The TSA timestamp matches the envelope
signature (not the log entry's signature), so it should not produce a
timestamp failure. Exploits the fact that ECDSA produces different
signatures for the exact same input.

Construction:
  1. Sign in-toto statement A as DSSE → bundle1 (happy-path source)
  2. Sign the same statement A as DSSE again with the same ECDSA key and
     same Fulcio-issued certificate → bundle2
  3. In bundle1, replace the envelope signature and the RFC3161 timestamps
     with those from bundle2.

Signed against staging Sigstore using the
sigstore-conformance/extremely-dangerous-public-oidc-beacon workflow
identity. The bundle ships its own trusted_root.json (the staging trust
root); once production has a Rekor v2 instance the custom trust root can
be removed.
